 1670|       |	 * into the kernel and *if* you're not on a system that doesn't
 1671|       |	 * allow them - some SELinux systems don't allow you create them.
 1672|       |	 * Most systems probably have them configured in, but not all systems
 1673|       |	 * have them configured in and allow them to be created.
